caption: The man got my order all wrong when I asked if he could fix it he told me NO and hung up on me, I went back to the store and he talked on the phone and was very rude,just plane nasty my order was $40+ and he acted like I spent $2.00 never ever will I go there again

I've never experienced rudeness from the staff, but the food is just not good.  I normally get a wonton soup and it's pretty hard to mess that up, so it's usually decent.  However, last night I ordered shrimp egg foo yung and shrimp yat gaw mein.  My goodness, the food was awful!  It was devoid of any taste and heavy, heavy, heavy on the grease...to the point of leaving a greasy coating on the tongue. And let's not mention the soapy aftertaste. Yuck!   Both dishes were very difficult to get through...which I endeavored to do because I just hate wasting time and money.  They need people.  Stop being cheap and hire more (better) cooks, Peking House.  This is not a good look.
